### Test API Endpoints
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code
### Or use the commands below with curl/Postman

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

### Root Endpoint
GET http://localhost:5000/

### Add a Reading (ESP32 simulation)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/readings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "ESP32_001",
  "voltage": 220.5,
  "current": 2.3,
  "power": 507.15,
  "energy": 0.0007,
  "location": "Home",
  "appliance": "Lighting"
}

### Get Latest Reading
GET http://localhost:5000/api/readings/latest

### Get Today's Readings
GET http://localhost:5000/api/readings/today

### Get This Month's Readings
GET http://localhost:5000/api/readings/month

### Get Dashboard Summary
GET http://localhost:5000/api/dashboard/summary

### Get Real-time Stats
GET http://localhost:5000/api/dashboard/realtime

### Get Today's Cost
GET http://localhost:5000/api/cost?period=today

### Get Cost Prediction
GET http://localhost:5000/api/cost/prediction?period=month

### Get Cost Comparison
GET http://localhost:5000/api/cost/comparison?period=month

### Get Appliance Data
GET http://localhost:5000/api/appliances?period=today

### Get Specific Appliance
GET http://localhost:5000/api/appliances/Lighting?period=today
